
Here are 40 commonly used commands for managing Kubernetes clusters:

kubectl version: Display the client and server Kubernetes version.
kubectl cluster-info: Display cluster information.
kubectl get pods: List all pods in the current namespace.
kubectl get deployments: List all deployments in the current namespace.
kubectl get services: List all services in the current namespace.
kubectl get nodes: List all nodes in the cluster.
kubectl describe pod [pod_name]: Describe details about a specific pod.
kubectl describe deployment [deployment_name]: Describe details about a specific deployment.
kubectl describe service [service_name]: Describe details about a specific service.
kubectl describe node [node_name]: Describe details about a specific node.
kubectl create -f [filename]: Create resources from a YAML file.
kubectl apply -f [filename]: Apply changes to resources from a YAML file.
kubectl delete -f [filename]: Delete resources defined in a YAML file.
kubectl exec -it [pod_name] -- [command]: Execute a command inside a pod.
kubectl logs [pod_name]: Display logs for a specific pod.
kubectl scale deployment [deployment_name] --replicas=[number]: Scale a deployment to a specific number of replicas.
kubectl edit pod [pod_name]: Edit a pod configuration.
kubectl edit deployment [deployment_name]: Edit a deployment configuration.
kubectl rollout restart deployment [deployment_name]: Restart a deployment.
kubectl get namespaces: List all namespaces in the cluster.
kubectl create namespace [namespace_name]: Create a new namespace.
kubectl describe namespace [namespace_name]: Describe details about a specific namespace.
kubectl delete namespace [namespace_name]: Delete a namespace.
kubectl config view: Display kubeconfig configuration.
kubectl config current-context: Display the current-context in the kubeconfig file.
kubectl config use-context [context_name]: Set the current-context in the kubeconfig file.
kubectl rollout status deployment [deployment_name]: Check the status of a deployment rollout.
kubectl create secret [type] [name] [data]: Create a secret.
kubectl get secret [secret_name]: Get details about a secret.
kubectl delete secret [secret_name]: Delete a secret.
kubectl get events: Display cluster events.
kubectl top node: Show metrics for nodes.
kubectl top pod: Show metrics for pods.
kubectl port-forward [pod_name] [local_port]:[remote_port]: Forward one or more local ports to a pod.
kubectl proxy: Run a proxy to the Kubernetes API server.
kubectl rollout history deployment [deployment_name]: Display rollout history of a deployment.
kubectl annotate [resource_type] [resource_name] [annotation_key]=[annotation_value]: Add an annotation to a resource.
kubectl label [resource_type] [resource_name] [label_key]=[label_value]: Add a label to a resource.
kubectl rollout undo deployment [deployment_name]: Undo a deployment to the previous version.
kubectl create -f [directory]: Create resources from all YAML files in a directory.
